cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with prosodic entrainment in cooperative game dialogs and presents entrainment profiles to detect within- and across-dialog entrainment by the speakers' gender and role in the game. Other likely sub-categories include cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper deals with the rhythmic and cooperative aspects of speech. Additionally, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) could also be possible sub-categories as the paper uses feature sets and entrainment profiles to analyze the data.
